<subSubSection id="DF89B417BFEF38B01EA5BE1EF531C1BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FD4DC0B00179F2A639ACBE10AF2AA407" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6EAC5F813E04E11AC3E08790B9A26EC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
In the present study, no culture could be obtained for 
<taxonomicName id="44C667B0A7A71CC5D0657F4D0C51953F" genus="D." lsidName="D. ravennica" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" rank="species" species="ravennica">
<emphasis id="B30B70E3256BC79CD32FA3B627D60C5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">D. ravennica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
despite several trials on various media including MEA, potato dextrose agar, corn meal agar or water agar at different incubation conditions, the reason for which the species was subjected to direct DNA extraction from conidiomata. 
<taxonomicName id="A191764D7406019B541F987A7AD69D2C" authorityName="Bundhun, Jeewon, Camporesi, J. C. Kang &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Coelomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Discosia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Discosia ravennica" order="Amphisphaeriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Deuteromycotina" rank="species" species="ravennica">
<emphasis id="7C4A6AB76BBAB9A2CFB58DB43AA91FEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Discosia ravennica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0BB4DA2975C13F4C276E9A82C01F0C3A" genus="D." lsidName="D. neofraxinea" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" rank="species" species="neofraxinea">
<emphasis id="FD9D58DC7951746FFD8159C435731ABB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">D. neofraxinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of superficial conidiomata, which are not glabrous and 3-septate conidia with cells of unequal length. It also closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="304216077CB71A84381656339B984DF6" genus="D." lsidName="D. fraxinea" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" rank="species" species="fraxinea">
<emphasis id="A502439C7F3BE31BFA44FFA946F67103" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">D. fraxinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schwein.) 
<bibRefCitation id="9A77C7396C52D43BBE471BDC371CDBCF" author="Nag Raj, TR" journalOrPublisher="Mycologue Publications, Waterloo, Canada" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" refId="B34" refString="Nag Raj, TR, 1993. Coelomycetous anamorphs with appendage-bearing conidia. Mycologue Publications, Waterloo, Canada" title="Coelomycetous anamorphs with appendage-bearing conidia." year="1993">Nag Raj (1993)</bibRefCitation>
in having uni-to bi-locular applanate conidiomata and naviculate to subcylindrical 3-septate conidia with cells of unequal length. The new species, however, also differs from the latter two species as mentioned in Table 
<tableCitation id="9FD6C5E85FC3118279E78623072BE1E2" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Features distinguishing Discosia ravennica, D. fraxinea and D. neofraxinea." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0AA38B1F27083E771A574A9FF506F6D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" tableUuid="0AA38B1F27083E771A574A9FF506F6D9">2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
